        <content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:1111/blog/hello-world/">&lt;p&gt;Every developer eventually writes a &quot;hello world&quot; post. Here&#x27;s mine.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;why-a-blog&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;zola-anchor&quot; href=&quot;#why-a-blog&quot; aria-label=&quot;Anchor link for: why-a-blog&quot;&gt;🔗&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;Why a blog?&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#x27;ve been meaning to start writing for a while. Not to build an audience or
sell anything — just to have a place to dump notes, document setups, and
occasionally think out loud.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The format is simple: things I find interesting, things I build, things I
break and then fix.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;why-zola&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;zola-anchor&quot; href=&quot;#why-zola&quot; aria-label=&quot;Anchor link for: why-zola&quot;&gt;🔗&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;Why Zola?&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Static sites are the right tool for personal blogs. No database, no moving
parts, fast deploys, easy backups. Zola is written in Rust, has zero runtime
dependencies, and builds in milliseconds.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo&quot; style=&quot;color: #F8F8F2; background-color: #282A36;&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;shellscript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #6272A4;&quot;&gt;# install on Arch&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #50FA7B;&quot;&gt;pacman&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #BD93F9;&quot;&gt; -S&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #F1FA8C;&quot;&gt; zola&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #6272A4;&quot;&gt;# build and serve locally&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #50FA7B;&quot;&gt;zola&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #F1FA8C;&quot;&gt; serve&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-to-expect&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;zola-anchor&quot; href=&quot;#what-to-expect&quot; aria-label=&quot;Anchor link for: what-to-expect&quot;&gt;🔗&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;What to expect&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Posts will mostly be about:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Linux system administration and configuration&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shell scripting and automation&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware tinkering&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software I find interesting&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No ads, no tracking, no JavaScript required to read a post.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&#x27;s it. Let&#x27;s get writing.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
